{"cursor":"10390","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Federal Ministry of Justice\n|nativename = Bundesministerium der Justiz (BMJ) |logo = BMJ Logo.svg\n|logo_width = 260 |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |picture\n= |picture_width= |formed = 1 January 1877 as Reichsjustizamt |preceding = Reich\nMinistry of Justice |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = Government of\nGermany |headquarters = MohrenstraÃe 37 10117 Berlin |coordinates =\n|employees = 623 |budget = |minister1_name = Sabine Leutheusser-Schnarrenberger\n|minister1_pfo = Federal Minister of Justice |chief1_name = Max Stadler\n|chief1_position= Parliamentary State Secretary |chief2_name = Birgit Grundmann\n|chief2_position= Permanent State Secretary |parent_agency = |child1_agency =\n|child2_agency = |website = http://www.bmj.bund.de |footnotes = }}\n\nThe 'Federal Ministry of Justice' (), abbreviated 'BMJ', is a cabinet-level\nministry of the Federal Republic of Germany. Under the German federal system,\nindividual States are most responsible for the administration of justice and the\napplication of penalties. The Federal Ministry of Justice devotes itself to\ncreating and changing law in the classic core areas related to Constitutional\nlaw. The Ministry also analyzes the legality and constitutionality of laws\nprepared by other ministries. The German Federal Court of Justice, the German\nPatent and Trade Mark Office (GPTO), and the German Patent Court all fall under\nits scope. The ministry is officially located in Berlin. Federal Ministry of\nJustice http://www.bmj.de/EN/FederalOffice/_node.html Official website]\nretrieved 1-Jun-2012\n\nThe BMJ was founded on January 1, 1877, as the Imperial Justice Office\n(Reichsjustizamt). After Germany became a republic in 1919, it was raised to the\nrank of a federal ministry as the Reichsministerium der Justiz. The ministry was\nformally renamed the Bundesministerium der Justiz in 1949. In several laws\npredating 1949, the ministry and the minister are however referred to as\nReichsministerium der Justiz and Reichsminister der Justiz, respectively. This\nhas gradually been replaced with the new name and title when laws have been\namended, most recently in 2010. [http://www.bgbl.de/Xaver/text.xav?bk=Bunde-\nsanzeiger_BGBl&start=%2F%2F*%5B%40attr_id%3D'bgbl110s1864.pdf'%5D&wc=1&skin=WC\nBGBL/de]\n","linknr":261,"url":"German_Ministry_of_Justice","recorded":1375070839,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Federal_Ministry_of_Justice_(Germany)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Federal_Ministry_of_Justice_(Germany)&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Federal_Ministry_of_Justice_(Germany)","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=German_Ministry_of_Justice&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:BMJ_Logo.svg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/BMJ_Logo.svg/260px-BMJ_Logo.svg.png","/wiki/Government_of_Germany","/wiki/Berlin","/wiki/Sabine_Leutheusser-Schnarrenberger","/wiki/Secretary_of_State#Germany","/wiki/Secretary_of_State#Germany","http://www.bmj.bund.de","/wiki/File:Bundesministerium_der_justiz.hauptsitz.eingangsbereich.JPG","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Bundesministeriu